Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Toss @butternut squash{12%ounce} on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon} and 1/2 TBSP @maple syrup{1%unit}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast until starting to brown, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Trim @Brussels sprouts{8%ounce}, then cut in half through the stem. Slice halves into thin ribbons across the stems. Pick @sage{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems and thinly slice.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add Brussels sprouts, season generously with salt and pepper, and cook until softened and starting to brown, ~{3-5%minutes}. Remove from pan and set aside.

Place @gnocchi{9%ounce} in boiling water, and cook until tender, ~{3-4%minutes}, or until they float. Drain.

While gnocchi cooks, add @butter{2%tablespoon} and 1/2 TBSP maple syrup to pan over medium-high heat. Season generously with salt and pepper. Add sage and stir until butter turns foamy and begins to brown, about ~{2%minutes}. Remove from heat.

Toss cooked butternut squash and Brussels sprouts into pan with sauce. Gently add gnocchi, season with salt and pepper, and stir to combine.